meta.meta: Toledo-Piza, M., G. M. T. Mattox, and R. Britz (2014). Priocharax nanus, a new miniature characid from the rio Negro, Amazon basin (Ostariophysi: Characiformes), with an updated list of miniature Neotropical freshwater fishes. Neotropical Ichthyology 12(2): 229-246

state.label: Priocharax nanus is distinguished from P. ariel and P. pygmaeus by the presence of i,6 pelvic fin rays
all jaw teeth small, conical and lingually curved to a moderate extent
incompletely divided longitudinally, articulating anteriorly with vertically elongated scapulocoracoid cartilage and posteriorly with larval-like pectoral-fin fold supported only by actinotrichia
Endoskeletal bones of pectoral girdle absent, exoskeletal part with posttemporal, supracleithrum, cleithrum and two postcleithra
Weberian apparatus well developed, all components ossified
Hooks absent in dorsal-, pectoral-, pelvic-, and anal-fins of all examined specimens
presence of two postcleithra; unclear if the dorsal postcleithrum of P. nanus represents postcleithrum 1 or 2
Relatively shorter caudal peduncle (13.5-16.8% SL) in P. nanus
Caudal peduncle 18.1- 23.7 % SL in P. ariel
Priocharax nanus has a dentary tooth count of 33-40, intermediate between that of P. ariel and P. pygmaeus with some overlap on each end of the range
